description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Staff Nurses to join our friendly and caring hospital team here at Clifton Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking to recruit a number of permanent Band 5 Registered Nurses (full and part-time hours considered) to work as part of our motivated and supportive team here at Clifton Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clifton Hospital is a nurse and therapy rehabilitation unit on the Fylde Coast in-between St Anne&#39;s and Lytham. We are passionate about going the extra mile for our patients and as a team we ensure the patient is at the centre of all we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently have 106 in-patient beds spread across 4 wards. Each ward has a supportive Ward Manager and two Band 6 Sisters/Charge Nurses leading the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The teams here at Clifton Hospital work in a Multidisciplinary way with input from dedicated and experienced Advanced Practitioners, Physiotherapists and Occupational Therapists as well as the Hospital Discharge Team on site. This means we ensure that our patient care is delivered safely, effectively and compassionately with the patient at the centre of what we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Anyone interested in joining our team must display an enthusiastic and dynamic approach in caring for our patients. As a permanent fixture in our team you must be adaptable and willing to learn and develop within the role. This is a fully rotational post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our commitment to you is to provide the environment for this to happen and ensure that you are supported in your role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSophie PendletonJob titleWard managerEmail addresssophie.pendleton@nhs.netTelephone number01253 955408Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like and further information then please contact the Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
